Their sprawling six-bed US pile, built in 1929, boasts 11,000 sq ft of living space. Prince of Darkness Ozzy, 73, and former X Factor judge Sharon, 69, aim to be based at their Buckinghamshire pile, Welders House. The dad of five, who had back surgery last month, has said: "We are leaving LA. We are a bit sad. But the tax is getting too much." Revealing his plans here, he added: "I am going to build a barn there and make my own studio. I will still be making music and my band will come over." The ex-frontman of Black Sabbath, who has fought mobility issues and has Parkinson's, has delayed his European tour with Judas Priest until 2023. 